Package utam.lightning.pageobjects

Interface Input

  • All Superinterfaces:
    utam.core.framework.base.PageObject, utam.core.framework.base.UtamBase
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InputImpl
    public interface Input
extends utam.core.framework.base.PageObject
    Selector: lightning-input Represents the lightning-input Lightning web component. Check if it has a label and get the label text. Check if the element has focus. Get the text value and set the text by scrolling to the input field. Toggle the checkbox or set the required status if the component contains a checkbox. Get the checked status. Check if there are any errors, and get the error text. Select the radio button if the component has a radio button. Select the date and time if the component has date and time pickers. Check if the input is enabled, or if it's read only. , created from JSON resources/utam/lightning/input.utam.json
    Version:
    1.2.0
    Author:
    Salesforce
